# Ollama Uncensored Offline Pentesting Assistant

A fully **offline, uncensored** version of Ollama fine-tuned and system-prompted specifically for **penetration testing** and red team operations.

This project provides a local, private AI assistant that helps with pentesting tasks without sending any data to the cloud, without content filters, and without rate limits.

### Why I Built This
While working on my home lab (Kali Linux, Windows agents, RDP brute-force testing, SOC detection lab with ELK + Mythic C2, etc.), I needed a reliable AI helper that could:
- Assist with command generation
- Explain techniques and vulnerabilities
- Help craft payloads and scripts
- Suggest enumeration steps
- Analyze logs or errors
- Brainstorm attack paths

...all while staying completely **air-gapped** and **uncensored**.

### Features
- **100% Offline** — Runs entirely on your local machine
- **Uncensored** — No safety refusals on security-related topics
- Customized system prompts optimized for pentesting, red teaming, and offensive security
- Easy one-click setup (Ollama + Modelfile)
- Supports popular models (llama3, mistral, phi3, gemma2, etc.)
- Tailored for real-world use cases: reconnaissance, exploitation, post-exploitation, evasion, reporting, etc.

### Tech Stack
- Ollama
- Custom Modelfile with specialized system instructions
- Optional: Open WebUI for a clean ChatGPT-like interface

### Use Cases
- Generating reverse shells and payloads
- Helping with Crowbar/Hydra/Metasploit usage
- Explaining Windows/Linux privilege escalation
- Creating detection evasion techniques
- Brainstorming lateral movement and C2 setups (like Mythic C2)
- Writing custom scripts and tools
- Reviewing scan results or logs

**Important Note**: This tool is intended strictly for authorized penetration testing, red team exercises, and educational purposes in controlled lab environments.

---

Built as a personal pentesting companion for current and future project
